  "prompt": "How do I turn off screen overlay in Android?",
  "response": "To turn off screen overlay in Android, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to Settings on your Android device\n\n2. Tap on \"Apps\" or \"Application Manager\"\n\n3. Tap the three-dot menu or overflow icon\n\n4. Select \"Special access\" or \"Special app access\"\n\n5. Look for \"Display over other apps\" or \"Draw over other apps\"\n\n6. Find the app causing the overlay and toggle it off\n\nAlternative method:\n1. Go to Settings\n2. Tap \"Security\" or \"Biometrics and Security\"\n3. Find \"Display over other apps\"\n4. Turn off apps causing overlay\n\nIf you can't access settings due to overlay:\n1. Go to Settings\n2. Tap \"Apps\"\n3. Find the app causing overlay\n4. Select \"Force stop\"\n5. Then disable the app's permission to draw over other apps\n\nNote: The exact steps might vary slightly depending on your Android version and device manufacturer.\n\nIf you're getting a \"Screen overlay detected\" error:\n1. Disable all apps with overlay permission\n2. Turn them on one by one to identify the problematic app",
